    <text id="A0573T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Cochran reflects on the meaning of South Carolina's secession. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mother</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-12-21"><abbr expan="December">Decr</abbr> 21<hi
                                rend="super">st</hi> 60 </date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Mother </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your letter was received on the 19<hi rend="super">th</hi>. I will send Franks
                    gun up on monday by the express train. There is nothing talked about here but
                    that all absorbing <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> subject secession. South Carolina has
                    gloriously vindicated her honor. She has passed her ordinance of secession and
                    henceforth the 20<hi rend="super">th</hi> day of December will be as glorious a
                    day for the South as ever the 4<hi rend="super">th</hi> of July was to the
                    United States. We speak now of the United States as of a nation that has <hi
                        rend="underline">passed</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">away</hi> as of a government that has lived out its
                    allotted time and passed away into the dim past. More glorious things are
                    looming up in the now <hi rend="underline">near</hi> future. </p>

                <p>Enclosed I send your bill. Mr. D. gave me $25. I would send the change but it
                    would not be safe I will bring it up with me when I come. As you see it is
                    $2.85.</p>

                <p>Give my respects to all my friends. Hoping all are well I remain your
                    affectionate son.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute> </salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="John">J.</abbr> H. Cochran </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P.S. Franks letter was received today I will answer soon
                        it was missent. J.H.C. </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
